   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Internet Service &amp; Allowances for Myanmar Teachers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Feb 2021 military coup &amp; COVID-19 in Myanmar have caused a humanitarian crisis. The population is facing food shortages, lack of access to education, losses of jobs, and a health crisis. Inflation has jumped to 40% within 8 months and the economy has shrunk considerably. Schools and universities are still closed due to the political crisis and COVID-19 outbreak. The National University of the University of Myanmar (NUUM) provides educational opportunities for Myanmar students &amp; teachers.</narrative>
  </description>
